Executive summary

Attendance is overwhelmingly local to regional, not destination-driven. About 81% of registrations come from within 30 miles of Allerton, including 55.0% from the 16–30 mile band and 25.8% from the 0–15 mile band. Only 18.0% come from beyond 30 miles, with just 5.9% from 60+ miles. Total registrations across distance bands are 5,792.

The business is anchored by a tight Illinois catchment area, especially ZIP codes in the 618xx corridor. The largest registration ZIPs are:
61856 (782), 61821 (653), 61822 (608), 61820 (391), 61801 (379), 61853 (313), 62521 (225), 61802 (199), 61874 (158), and 62526 (96).
These are the ZIPs that matter most in the current view. The exhibits do not provide a clean county breakout, and they also do not give an exact Illinois-vs-out-of-state attendee share. That said, the map strongly suggests the audience is predominantly Illinois-based, with a relatively small out-of-state tail.

Revenue follows the same pattern: the biggest revenue-driving geographies are also the core nearby ZIPs. The top 10 ZIPs by revenue are:
61856 ($54,745), 61821 ($39,332), 61822 ($35,015), 61801 ($27,340), 61820 ($24,430), 61853 ($20,629), 62521 ($15,385), 61802 ($14,100), 61874 ($11,750), and 62526 ($6,480).
By distance band, nearby regional attendees (16–30 miles) generate the most revenue at $214,345, followed by local attendees (0–15 miles) at $103,832. Total revenue across bands is $394,782.

Repeat behavior is strongest closest to Allerton. Local attendees have the highest repeat rate at 56.9%, followed by nearby regional at 53.1%, extended regional at 51.9%, destination at 51.4%, and unknown at 50.0%. This suggests loyalty is highest in the immediate trade area and declines modestly with distance.

On the question of whether premium classes pull from farther away, the available evidence says not really. Average spend is highest for local attendees at $188, then drops to $150 for nearby regional, $148 for extended regional, and $125 for destination attendees. That pattern suggests the strongest monetization is still coming from the nearby base, not from far-traveling attendees. If anything, higher-value participation appears to be more local than destination-led.



- Audience is overwhelmingly local/regional: 81% of registrations come from within 30 miles.
- Core demand is concentrated in nearby Illinois ZIPs, especially the 618xx corridor.
- The same ZIPs lead both registrations and revenue, led by 61856, 61821, and 61822.
- Revenue is driven most by the 16–30 mile band, then the 0–15 mile band.
- Repeat rates are strongest among local attendees and taper slightly with distance.
- Premium spend does not skew farther away; local attendees have the highest average spend.
